to bear stearns in a transaction that was exempt
from registration under the securities act of 1933,
pursuant to section4(2) thereof, in exchange for
95.0million newly issued shares of bear stearns
common stock (or 39.5% of bear stearns common stock
after giving effect to the issuance). upon the
consummation of the bear stearns merger, on may30,
2008, the 20.7million shares of jpmorgan chase
common stock and 95million shares of bear stearns
common stock were cancelled. for a further
discussion of this transaction, see note 2 on pages
123128 of this annual report.
